SIMPLE: mealy-mouthed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mealy-mouthed
<hw>Meal"y-mouthed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Using soft
words; not straightforward; plausible; affectedly or timidly delicate of
speech; speaking deviously; unwilling to tell the truth in plain
language. Opposite of <ant>frank</ant> or <ant>blunt</ant>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Mealy-mouthed</xex> philanthropies.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She was a fool to be <qex>mealy-mouthed</qex> where nature speaks
so plain.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Meal"y-mouth`ness</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mean</ent>⟦br⟧
